<TITLE> 4 die in 3 accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)Four persons were killed in two road accidents in Madaripur and Magura. Madaripur bdnews24.com correspondent reports that a bus ran over two motor bike passengers at Senrpara on the Dhaka-Barisal Highway of Rajair upazila at around 11.30am on Saturday. The deceased were identified as Dulal Khalasi, 35, a fertiliser trader, and Tapan Dey, 37, Madaripur section's marketing manager of Aftab Group. Mashiur Rahman, OC of the Rajair Police Station, told journalists that the accident occurred when a Barisal-bound bus ran over a motor bike, coming from opposite side. Rahman said that Dulal died on the spot and the injured Tapan died on the way to Rajair Upazila Health Complex. A case has been filed with the police station in this regard, the police officer added. bdnews24.com's Magura correspondent reported that two persons were killed in two traffic accidents in Magura on Friday night. The deceased were Ohiduzzaman, 35, and an unidentified woman, 30. Magura Sadr Police chief Mizanur Rahman told journalists that a truck ran over Ohiduzzaman when he was crossing the road at Chhoto Bridge area on the Magura-Jhenaidah Highway at around 8pm. The police brought him to Magura Sadr Hospital where the duty doctor declared him dead, the police offficer added. Mizanur Rahman said that an identified mad woman was crushed by a truck at Belnagar on the Magura-Faridpur Highway at around 10.30pm. Both the trucks escaped. Two cases were filed with the Magura Sadr Police Station. bdnew
